From 795a60406722d279ef0c463a53597db68f6d5ac8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Vishwaroop A <va@nvidia.com>
Date: Tue, 14 May 2024 09:31:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 28/95] NVIDIA: SAUCE: s25fs: Add post-get-map-id fixup

BugLink: https://bugs.launchpad.net/bugs/2080908

Add a post-get-map-id fixup for S25FS512S flash devices. The fixup
reads the values of the CR3V and CR1V registers and determines the map ID
based on those values. The fixup also checks for invalid combinations of
CR3V and CR1V values and returns 0 in those cases.

This fixup is necessary to workaround an issue with the SFDP Address Map
for S25FS512S flash devices. The SFDP Address Map for these devices
incorrectly reports that the map ID is 0 when it should be 1. This
issue can cause problems when trying to erase sectors on the flash device.

The fixup in this commit will force the flash device to use the first
sector address map, which is the correct map for S25FS512S flash devices.

http://nvbugs/4218915

